review_blob: Its been a while since I had this fresh, in Germany, but oh boy was it good.  This is a lot like pilsener Urquell, but sweeter/maltier.  Im anxious to try it now that it will be here in the USA.
Like all mass produced American pilseners, this beer has nothing to offer in flavor, aroma, or body.  Give me a diet coke if this is all youve got in beer.

This beer just doesnt do it for me.  Maybe I have something against hype, as this beer is hyped a lot, but it just tastes harsh and unpleasant to me.  Sorry, guys.  I do like your IPA quite well, however.
Not a bad pale ale.  Maybe too much caramel flavor in it?  Hops decent.  I wouldnt turn one down if it was offered.

This beer is nothing like the wit beers I have had in Belgium.  This was thin, lacking in the proper phenolics for a true Belgian wit beer.  They should call it a wheat ale with a little citrus character added.
Fantastic pale ale.  Almost as good as Burning Bird.  Beautiful hop flavor and aroma, excellent and clean malt character.

I do not think that the belgian yeast flavor goes at all with this beer.  I first tasted this beer with such anticipation as I heard so much good about it.  What a letdown!  There were 3 of us and we couldnt even finish 1/2 of a bottle.  I dont see what the deal is with this beer.
The bottle I got was quite flat.  Just a little carbonation.  The beer was all bitterness, no hop flavor and aroma.  Very one sided, not enjoyable.  Maybe it would be better if it werent flat.
Dont care for the overly smokey character of the beer.  Some off flavor in there I dont care for either.  Not too bad, I guess.
beer_name: Four Peaks Kilt Lifter Scottish Style Ale

review_blob: Really good.  I got a lot of hop flavor and hop aroma.  Malty flavor, too.
This stout is silky smooth, rich, and deceiving.  You cant tell how strong it is until you feel it.  A truly great imperial stout.
Hops really come through.  Mmmmmm!  Malty, too!
